1
00:00:01,209 --> 00:00:03,253
<i>I cut the CCTV connection, Boss Emil.</i>

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:06,715
<i>Listen, okay? We aren't done yet.</i>

3
00:00:06,798 --> 00:00:08,675
[CABRAL] <i>What's the situation inside?</i>

4
00:00:08,758 --> 00:00:10,969
<i>We were able to tap into</i>
<i>the security cameras earlier,</i>

5
00:00:11,052 --> 00:00:12,053
<i>but we lost the feed.</i>

6
00:00:13,513 --> 00:00:15,181
<i>- Hey!</i>
- [MINNIE WHIMPERS]

7
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:17,684
- [MIKE] <i>We have a child. Please--</i>
- [ROMAN] <i>I don't care!</i>

8
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:20,145
[IVAN] <i>Why is the name</i>
<i>written here different?</i>

9
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:22,230
<i>I need to review her chart.</i>

10
00:00:22,313 --> 00:00:23,857
<i>I'll check the hospital records.</i>

11
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:25,775
<i>Just treat her.</i>

12
00:00:27,777 --> 00:00:28,945
<i>Boss Emil.</i>

13
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,739
<i>The building is secured.</i>

14
00:00:30,822 --> 00:00:33,616
<i>Thank you for being obedient,</i>
<i>General Cabral.</i>

15
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:37,037
<i>Are you sure all your men</i>
<i>left the building?</i>

16
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:37,996
<i>Yes, I'm sure.</i>

17
00:00:38,496 --> 00:00:40,290
<i>I thought there were no cops</i>
<i>left in the building.</i>

18
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:42,584
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GROANS]

19
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:47,589
[MEN GRUNTING]

20
00:00:47,672 --> 00:00:50,091
- [WENDY SCREAMS]
- [FREDO, MAGNUS GRUNTING]

21
00:00:50,175 --> 00:00:51,468
[MAGNUS SCREAMS]

22
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:52,844
<i>Go ahead!</i>

23
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:55,055
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GROANS]

24
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,682
<i>You'll pay for everything you've done!</i>

25
00:00:57,766 --> 00:00:59,559
<i>Good for you.</i>

26
00:01:00,268 --> 00:01:02,228
<i>Your family is all together.</i>

27
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:04,064
<i>But it's okay.</i>

28
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:06,399
<i>Soon, all of my family</i>
<i>will be together too.</i>

29
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:09,527
[ROMAN]<i> Boss Emil, I brought you a gift.</i>

30
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:11,821
<i>You'll be useful to me.</i>

31
00:01:13,156 --> 00:01:14,407
<i>And you?</i>

32
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:17,077
<i>You might be useful to me too.</i>

33
00:01:18,119 --> 00:01:20,789
<i>Don't strap bombs on them yet.</i>

34
00:01:21,581 --> 00:01:23,166
<i>Where's the pharmacy?</i>

35
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:25,251
<i>- Where is it?!</i>
<i>- This way. Follow me.</i>

36
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:32,967
[IVAN] This is it.

37
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:35,470
- Relax. Just follow me.
- Hurry.

38
00:01:36,846 --> 00:01:37,806
Hurry!

39
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:44,854
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:52,070
Get the meds needed. Go!

41
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:57,450
We're in a hurry!

42
00:01:57,534 --> 00:02:03,331
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

43
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,710
[RUSTLING]

44
00:02:08,753 --> 00:02:10,004
Faster!

45
00:02:11,714 --> 00:02:15,677
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

46
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:17,095
[HOMER] Hurry! Move!

47
00:02:17,178 --> 00:02:18,346
This one.

48
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:23,601
Come on, let's go.

49
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:29,691
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:02:34,904 --> 00:02:37,574
[PLASTIC RUSTLING]

51
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:42,495
[CLINKS]

52
00:02:46,374 --> 00:02:51,129
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

53
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:52,213
Let's go!

54
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:54,757
All right.

55
00:02:56,426 --> 00:02:57,677
Keep walking. Go.

56
00:02:57,760 --> 00:03:02,974
[LIGHT FOOTSTEPS]

57
00:03:03,057 --> 00:03:03,933
[THUD]

58
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:05,310
You're so clumsy!

59
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:06,769
[IVAN GRUNTS]

60
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:08,771
[GROANS]

61
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:16,779
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [LUNA AND HOMER GRUNTING]

62
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:23,453
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GRUNTING]

63
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:24,454
- [GUNSHOTS]
- Doc!

64
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:25,914
[BULLET HITS FLESH]

65
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:28,750
[MUSIC BECOMES MOROSE]

66
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:29,834
[LUNA GASPS]

67
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:45,350
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:17,465
[IVAN] Luna!

69
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,175
[LUNA BREATHES SHARPLY]

70
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:27,308
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

71
00:04:35,191 --> 00:04:36,317
[GUN CLATTERS]

72
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:44,742
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

73
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:56,713
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

74
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:04,470
Nurse, I'll leave her to you. Thank you.

75
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:12,603
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

76
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:24,282
[LINE RINGING]

77
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:26,159
- [PHONE BUZZING]
- [KEYPAD BEEPS]

78
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:29,871
Mila? Is there a problem?

79
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:31,873
Get out of there.

80
00:05:31,956 --> 00:05:35,710
Mila, if you want me
to get out of here alive,

81
00:05:35,793 --> 00:05:36,961
you'll help us.

82
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,963
Lucas, I can't do this anymore.

83
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:42,425
You can do this. We can do this.

84
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:48,681
We need to make this sacrifice
to give our child a better life.

85
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:49,974
[SIGHS]

86
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:54,479
Do what Boss Emil tells you to do.

87
00:05:54,562 --> 00:05:57,482
You'll be our eyes and ears outside.

88
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:01,319
Find out what the police are up to.

89
00:06:01,402 --> 00:06:02,403
Bye.

90
00:06:04,363 --> 00:06:06,824
[SIGHS, BREATHES SHARPLY]

91
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:13,039
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:22,256
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:39,190
[LUNA GROANING IN PAIN]

94
00:06:39,273 --> 00:06:42,819
[LUNA BREATHING HEAVILY]

95
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:43,820
[IVAN GRUNTS]

96
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:46,114
[IVAN] We need to remove the bullet.

97
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:47,990
You have to trust me, okay?

98
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:49,450
[LUNA] Okay.

99
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:58,417
- [LABORED BREATHING]
- [UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

100
00:06:58,501 --> 00:06:59,919
[WHIMPERS]

101
00:07:00,002 --> 00:07:06,717
- [LABORED BREATHING]
- [UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:16,686
[LUNA WHIMPERS]

103
00:07:19,063 --> 00:07:21,607
You're starting to feel the anesthesia.

104
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:24,110
That's normal.

105
00:07:24,193 --> 00:07:25,778
You're doing great, Luna.

106
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:30,199
[CHUCKLES]

107
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,827
You're kind of suggestive too, Doc.

108
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:33,911
How so?

109
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:40,042
You're doubting my friendship with Liam?

110
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:42,795
We're just friends, Doc.

111
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:47,300
He's like a brother to me.

112
00:07:47,383 --> 00:07:50,761
Liam… Seriously?

113
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:53,222
He's really handsome, Doc.

114
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:56,142
[MONITOR BEEPING]

115
00:07:56,225 --> 00:07:57,602
But you're more handsome, Doc.

116
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:02,982
Are you single? I'm single too.

117
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,318
Let's date.

118
00:08:05,401 --> 00:08:12,283
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:08:20,249 --> 00:08:21,959
[MUSIC FADES]

120
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:29,008
- Come on, move!
- Where are you taking me?

121
00:08:29,091 --> 00:08:30,927
Just come with us! Hurry!

122
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:36,224
- [MIKE] Take me! Not my wife!
- You have work to do for us.

123
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:38,559
- Boss, take me. Not her.
- [EMIL] Take him away.

124
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:40,728
- [FREDO] Hurry! Move!
- [MIKE] Wait! Wait, wait!

125
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,687
Wait!

126
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:46,234
That's too rough! You're hurting us!

127
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:55,826
There could be issues

128
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:59,914
if you and Dado
take our millions from the island.

129
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:03,584
- Boss, we've got the senator.
- Macky, what did you get into?

130
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:06,587
[DADO] The cops are under our control.

131
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:08,881
Dado's right.

132
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:12,134
We can do whatever we want.

133
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:15,012
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

134
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:16,305
[PHONE RINGING]

135
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:21,978
What is it, Conrad?

136
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:27,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

137
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:31,070
Are there still police guarding Jacinto?

138
00:09:31,153 --> 00:09:37,285
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:42,748
No. There's another problem.

140
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,501
A big one.

141
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:52,717
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:57,888
[REPORTER ON TV]<i> Authorities</i>
<i>confirm that the hostage takers</i>

143
00:09:57,972 --> 00:10:02,226
<i>are holding Sen. Eduardo Maristella,</i>
<i>his son Macky Maristella,</i>

144
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:07,189
<i>La Playa Roja owner Greta Roja,</i>
<i>and her son, Liam Roja.</i>

145
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:10,026
They've got Olsen too.

146
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:11,360
And Rita.

147
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:16,991
<i>Police say there may still be civilians</i>
<i>inside St. John's Hospital.</i>

148
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:21,037
<i>Three hostage takers have been identified.</i>

149
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:25,291
<i>Emilio Padua, Diosdado Menor,</i>
<i>and Lucas Sebastian.</i>

150
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:29,545
What are the police doing?
Why are they letting this happen?

151
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:32,673
They can't risk doing anything
when there are hostages.

152
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:36,427
What more do they want? Money again?

153
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,596
Wasn't the ransom money they got enough?

154
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:41,807
You know, I don't care what they're after.

155
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:45,519
What matters is that we get out of here
while we still have the chance.

156
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:47,980
What did you say? Huh?

157
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:50,775
You don't care? Huh?

158
00:10:50,858 --> 00:10:53,069
You don't even care about Sir Liam?

159
00:10:53,819 --> 00:10:55,237
[STAFF WHIMPERING]

160
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,156
- [WOMAN]<i> Sir Liam?</i>
<i>- Sir Liam!</i>

161
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:58,240
[STAFF SOB HAPPILY]

162
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:00,368
<i>I'm here to save you.</i>

163
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:01,369
<i>Sir…</i>

164
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:03,996
[GRUNTING, BLOWS LANDING]

165
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,498
[STAFF SCREAM]

166
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:12,254
- <i>Liam!</i>
- [GUNSHOTS]

167
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:18,010
Let me remind you, he risked his life
so that we could escape.

168
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:21,597
Joy, he saved us.

169
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,516
Did you forget that?

170
00:11:23,599 --> 00:11:25,643
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

171
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:29,021
Olsen did the same for me.

172
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:33,734
They didn't abandon us,
but now we're going to abandon them?

173
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:38,030
Of course I don't want to,
but we don't have a choice.

174
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:40,157
We'll find another way.

175
00:11:42,576 --> 00:11:45,579
What, feeling guilty now?

176
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:46,664
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

177
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:50,876
We don't have a choice
about that either. Look.

178
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,171
[BEEPING]

179
00:11:54,755 --> 00:12:00,428
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:12:04,974 --> 00:12:05,933
Liam.

181
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:13,357
Why did you say earlier
that we might be brothers?

182
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:17,319
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:12:18,612 --> 00:12:20,489
Sorry, I didn't know he heard.

184
00:12:22,241 --> 00:12:25,578
But isn't it better
if we all know the truth?

185
00:12:25,661 --> 00:12:26,620
What truth?

186
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:29,790
Liam.

187
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:33,127
That's not true.

188
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:38,132
Greta.

189
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:41,802
Whatever you're thinking, it isn't true.

190
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:42,928
Ma, come on.

191
00:12:46,056 --> 00:12:47,975
Why would Ma'am Greta even think that?

192
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,686
[OLSEN] Huh?

193
00:12:50,769 --> 00:12:54,565
Because your mother and my husband
had an affair.

194
00:12:54,648 --> 00:13:00,196
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

195
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:09,288
Son…

196
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:11,790
That was a long time ago.

197
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,376
A long time ago, and I regret it.

198
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:16,003
[SHAKY VOICE] Seriously?

199
00:13:20,841 --> 00:13:21,967
[MAGNUS] Olsen.

200
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:26,472
Liam.

201
00:13:30,726 --> 00:13:32,019
It was my fault.

202
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:36,482
We were drunk.

203
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:40,402
Why is it your fault? Did you force her?

204
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,656
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

205
00:13:44,865 --> 00:13:46,158
Ma…

206
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:48,702
[OLSEN EXHALES SHARPLY]

207
00:13:48,786 --> 00:13:50,204
That means…

208
00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:53,499
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:13:53,582 --> 00:13:56,210
…you were also his…

210
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:58,462
- Mistress.
- Mi--

211
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:01,173
You can't say it?

212
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:03,050
My husband's mistress.

213
00:14:06,845 --> 00:14:08,889
[WENDY SOBBING]

214
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,308
It was just one night, Greta.

215
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:16,730
The mother you adore so much
is not really a saint.

216
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:19,692
- [WENDY SNIFFLES]
- [MAGNUS] Enough.

217
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:21,610
Please, Greta, enough.

218
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:24,738
[GRETA BREATHING SHAKILY]

219
00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:26,532
What's the truth, Wendy?

220
00:14:26,615 --> 00:14:27,992
[WENDY SNIFFLES]

221
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:32,288
Wendy already explained everything to me.

222
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:36,667
I am not Olsen's father.

223
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:43,007
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:45,342
[EMIL] General Cabral lied to me.

225
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:46,927
What was he thinking?

226
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:49,513
That I wasn't serious about my threats?

227
00:14:51,181 --> 00:14:53,100
I will teach him a lesson.

228
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:56,103
I'm sorry,

229
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:58,647
but one of you

230
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:02,192
will have to fall from heaven

231
00:15:02,985 --> 00:15:05,029
and go to hell!

232
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:12,995
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:47,821
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:01,919
[LINE RINGING]

235
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:06,507
I knew it. You're also cunning, huh?

236
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:09,009
[EMIL] <i>You still have men</i>
<i>inside the hospital.</i>

237
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:13,013
I warned you before, didn't I?

238
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,598
Padua, calm down.

239
00:16:14,682 --> 00:16:17,226
My men just got stuck inside the hospital.

240
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:19,103
They're not a threat to you.

241
00:16:19,186 --> 00:16:20,938
Who are you trying to fool?

242
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:22,815
I'm true to my word.

243
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:25,776
I don't think you believe me,

244
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:28,237
so I'll give you a demonstration.

245
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:30,280
Padua. Padua, wait.

246
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:33,534
Just look up to the sky, General Cabral.

247
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:35,452
What?

248
00:16:35,536 --> 00:16:38,247
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

249
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:39,999
[POLICE SIREN BLARES]

250
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:05,315
Which one of you wants to show off
to those stubborn cops below?

251
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:10,946
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

252
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:16,577
I need a VIP.

253
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:25,127
Who here has wronged me?

254
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:38,348
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

255
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:39,850
- [GUNSHOT]
- [WOMEN SCREAM]

256
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,060
<i>Leni!</i>

257
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:42,603
- [LENI GROANS]
- [LIAM GRUNTS]

258
00:17:42,686 --> 00:17:43,687
[EMIL] <i>Leni!</i>

259
00:17:46,982 --> 00:17:50,819
I can finally make you pay
for what you did to my daughter.

260
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:54,573
There's even a bonus.

261
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:59,244
I can finally get back at your father too.

262
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:00,829
Not my son, please!

263
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:02,039
He's the one we're going to drop.

264
00:18:02,122 --> 00:18:04,875
- No! Leave my son alone!
- Pa!

265
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:07,419
- [MAGNUS GRUNTING]
- [LUCAS BREATHES DEEPLY]

266
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:09,588
- You know what, Boss Emil?
- [MAGNUS GRUNTS]

267
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:11,840
Let's make it more exciting.

268
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:16,261
- Magnus is my idol.
- [MAGNUS GRUNTS]

269
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:18,138
He's a total ladies' man.

270
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:21,391
Did you know there's a possibility
that Olsen is his son?

271
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:27,231
- [WENDY WHIMPERING]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:30,943
Son?

273
00:18:31,026 --> 00:18:32,319
[LUCAS CHUCKLES]

274
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:35,823
I found out from Liam Roja

275
00:18:35,906 --> 00:18:39,159
there's a possibility that
the security staff member is his brother.

276
00:18:39,243 --> 00:18:43,288
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WENDY WHIMPERING]

277
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:47,417
There's a possibility?

278
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,462
So, you're not sure?

279
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:52,840
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

280
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:54,591
Your son with whom?

281
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:57,803
With her?

282
00:18:59,054 --> 00:19:00,222
No.

283
00:19:00,722 --> 00:19:02,808
[WENDY SOBBING] No.

284
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:06,562
You really are an asshole!

285
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:09,940
My daughter wasn't your only victim.

286
00:19:10,023 --> 00:19:12,359
You toyed with a lot of women.

287
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:14,278
How many women did you toy with?

288
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:16,947
You deserve what's happening
to you right now.

289
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:19,950
I am your karma, you monster!

290
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:23,203
Just take it all out on me.

291
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:25,831
I'm the one who wronged you, aren't I?

292
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:27,457
[MAGNUS] I'm right here!

293
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:29,042
Come at me!

294
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:32,087
Leave them out of this!

295
00:19:32,629 --> 00:19:34,047
Take it all out on me!

296
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:37,885
Everyone will suffer
because of what you did!

297
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:40,762
I'll teach a lesson
not only to the police,

298
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:42,014
but to you as well!

299
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:48,145
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

300
00:19:52,357 --> 00:19:55,694
- [ROMAN] <i>You take care of them.</i>
- [GOON]<i> I said sit down!</i>

301
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:59,615
<i>Which of your two sons</i>
<i>are you going to choose to save,</i>

302
00:19:59,698 --> 00:20:02,451
<i>and which one will you leave to die?</i>

303
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:04,912
<i>One.</i>

304
00:20:04,995 --> 00:20:06,121
<i>Why are you hesitating?</i>

305
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:10,167
<i>Wendy said it herself!</i>
<i>Olsen is not your son.</i>

306
00:20:10,751 --> 00:20:13,420
- [WENDY] <i>Have mercy on Olsen.</i>
- [EMIL] <i>Seven!</i>

307
00:20:13,503 --> 00:20:17,841
<i>He's served you for years!</i>
<i>You know how much he loves you!</i>

308
00:20:17,925 --> 00:20:20,219
<i>Only one of them can live.</i>

309
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:21,553
<i>So make your choice.</i>

310
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:22,679
<i>Ten!</i>
